 :tx/rationale "Create task: CE-META: Meta-learning — phrasing pattern tracking and cross-project transfer. CONTEXT: The hypothesis ledger tracks predicted vs actual delta-F(S) but doesnt model WHY some hypotheses work better. No transfer of questioning strategy between projects. RATIONALE: Level 3 learning (meta-meta) — learn HOW to learn, not just WHAT. Questioning strategies are substrate-independent (C8) and transferable. ADR-CONVERGENCE-003. APPROACH: (1) Define PhrasingPattern enum in routing.rs: FilePathGrounded, FalsificationFramed, ObservationTextReusing, CrossPackageBridging, VoidExploring, BroadExploratory, SpecIdReferencing. (2) When generating a hypothesis in compile_hypothesis_prompt(), tag it with the PhrasingPattern used. Record as :hypothesis/phrasing-pattern datom alongside the existing hypothesis datoms. (3) In calibrate_phrasing_patterns(store), for each completed hypothesis (has actual delta-F(S)), group by phrasing pattern. Compute per-pattern: mean_delta_fs, count, accuracy (predicted vs actual). Store as :meta/pattern-{name} entity with :meta/pattern-weight (Double), :meta/pattern-accuracy (Double), :meta/pattern-count (Long). (4) In compile_hypothesis_prompt(), when selecting phrasing strategy, CONSULT the pattern weights. Higher-weight patterns are preferred at the current temperature. (5) Cross-project transfer: :meta/pattern-* datoms are ordinary datoms in the store. When stores are merged (CRDT), pattern weights from multiple projects combine. A new project can import pattern weights from a calibrated project store. (6) Bootstrap: initial pattern weights are uniform (1.0). After 10 hypothesis completions, weights begin to diverge. After 50, the pattern ranking stabilizes. ACCEPTANCE: (A) After 5 hypotheses with FalsificationFramed pattern, :meta/pattern-falsification-framed entity exists with count=5. (B) Pattern weights influence hypothesis phrasing selection. (C) Merging two stores combines pattern weights (average or Bayesian update). (D) Empty store has uniform weights (no bias). (E) Patterns are C8 substrate-independent — no domain-specific patterns. DEPENDS-ON: CE-TEMP (provides hypothesis generation), CE-COGNITION (provides calibration in cognitive loop). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/routing.rs (PhrasingPattern enum + calibrate_phrasing_patterns + pattern-aware compile_hypothesis_prompt)"
